                                                                                                               Anil frees pledged shares
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      Anil Ambani: Less burden                          
	Mumbai, Sept. 15: The Anil Dhirubhai Ambani group has revoked nearly 15 crore pledged shares in three companies  Reliance Capital Ltd, Reliance Communications and Reliance Infrastructure.        
	The shares have a combined market value of Rs 7,500 crore based on Tuesdays closing prices on the bourses.        
	The Anil Ambani group is, however, not the only conglomerate to press for the release of pledged shares.         
	In a clear indication that the promoters of companies now have the money to repay debts, Tata Sons recently revoked 4.1 million pledged shares of Tata Motors.        
	Similarly, one of the promoters of Suzlon Energy revoked four million shares, reducing the total shares pledged by the promoters.        
	In Reliance Capital (RCL), the promoter group reduced the shares pledged by them by 71.20 lakh shares, constituting 2.90 per cent of the outstanding capital of the company. Consequently, shares pledged by the promoter group came down to 1.13 per cent of the total number of outstanding shares of the company. The market value of these shares based on the closing price of RCL on the BSE today is put at Rs 652.19 crore        
	It may be recalled that in February, RCL had told the stock exchanges that AAA Enterprises Pvt Ltd, a promoter, had pledged 9,893,179 shares of RCL of the 126,389,839 shares it held in the company.        
	In Reliance Communication, the promoter group reduced the shares pledged by them by 11.32 crore shares, constituting 5.48 per cent of the outstanding capital of the company. R-Com said the shares pledged by the promoter group had been reduced to 7.71 per cent.         
	The market value of these shares based on the closing price of R-Com share at Rs 300.65 is Rs 3,403 crore        
	In Reliance Infrastructure, the promoter group reduced the shares pledged by them by 2.87 crore shares, constituting 12.73 per cent of the outstanding capital of the company. Reliance Infrastructure added that the shares pledged by the promoter group had reduced to 3.8 per cent. The market value of these shares stands at Rs 3,452 crore.                                                                                                                                        
